  "datePublished": "2025-12-26",
  "description": "Zero is the number that represents nothing — the quantity you have when you have none of something. It is at once the simplest and most profound of numbers. Every child learns to count from zero (or, historically, from one, because zero took a long time to earn its place). Mathematically, zero is the starting point for the natural numbers, the identity element for addition, and the annihilator for multiplication. It is the only number that is neither positive nor negative. It is a boundary, a balancing point, and a foundation.\n",
